reviews_data.review_text: D&D or Beetlejuice Monopoly you can find it here. I love that its located in an old bank. My daughter spent some on her money on a Pokemon model kit.

My husband and I love to go to buzz for Friday night Magic, the community is absolutely amazing. This is one of the few card and game shops where the employees work hard to ensure customers know the products, and feel welcome in the store. Every employee has been super kind and helpful, and they all put in a ton of effort to make sure to help anyone and ensure their store events are entertaining and successful. Absolutely love this store and the community it has built.
Best local spot they always have the packs and games I’m looking for, knowledgeable team and great gear as well.

I thoroughly enjoyed my time in Buzz City Games. Can't wait to go back tbh. They had a great selection of cards and games but the vault where things are stored is just so neat. I loved the staff, the building, the selection, the pricing. All of it. Wish I could rate them higher than 5 stars honestly.
Bought a box of cards on a third party site and was extremely pleased with the transaction. Incredibly fast shipping and perfect condition on arrival. Highly recommend.
This place is great for enthusiast of various CCGs and Tabletop games. I have been thier on Wednesday nights to play D&D adventurer’s league.

This shop deserves recognition. I purchased a highly valuable card from a guy on FB market place and the team at this shop verified the authenticity of the card for free and even gave me a hard card to take it home with.

They didn’t know me and they didn’t receive anything in the deal. If that’s not a shop that deserves your business, then I don’t know of one that does. 5 stars.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the high praise. We are more than happy to help.

reviews_data.review_text: They actually help you find what you are looking for. Large collection. Very nice and helpful staff.

Fantastic selection of games from Warhammer to Magic the gathering to your board game classics. Wonderful staff and excellent stock on pre-release items. I couldn't get what I wanted online or at other area stores but Buzz city had me covered. I did my first pre release event and the staff were helpful in answering my game questions and organizing the event. 10/10 will play and preorder here again.

Not giving them a one star review because the store is nice and I enjoy being a customer of theirs. Unfortunately, they set an expectation with me that I would have a Final Fantasy pre release kit for their Friday, June 6, event about a week and a half prior to the event start. They posted the reservation to my account and told by staff that I was all set and I would have a pre release kit for the event. I receive a call from Buzz City Staff about 4 hours before the event on June 6, that they were not supposed to do that and that I would have  to come in a purchase it before the event. I was still at work and wouldn’t be able to do so anytime soon. They assured  me that they would probably still have some before the start. Needless to say, that was not the case. I had been looking forward to playing the event at my home store only for the expectation that was given to me be made void. Once again , great store in my opinion, but definitely not great at maintaining expectations.
Awesome place, cool collection with lots of variety.   Staff was friendly and helpful. The place appears to be in an old bank, with old vaults and other interesting historical artifacts.
Fantastic board game selection. They have just the right spectrum of board games from light games to heavy euro type games.
Horrible customer service and shipment method
I love coming here, always good vibes with helpful, entertaining staff.
Super positive environment, loved talking to the employee with the long hair and septum ring. Was very helpful, knowledgeable, understanding and fun to talk to. They deserve your business
Great store with friendly, knowledgeable staff! Commander is every Friday night, come on down.

A great place to visit when looking for d&d items or even to get information on how to start playing. I get magic cards and when I have to I trade them in but I enjoy the people there the most always friendly and helpful. They have lots of different events going on and new friends to meet.

One of the best sellers for MTG cards. I'd recommend them to anyone who wants reliable communication and the flexibility needed for a reputable seller. I'd recommend trying to purchase cards through them when possible.
We had a good time staff was excellent we would recommend

The store manager said that customer service isn’t important as she has a job to do. Why does she have a job in retail when she doesn’t care about customer service. How can I get in contact with the store owner. I spend a lot of money in the store and do not plan on returning because of her attuide!

My kids just started collecting cards. So I brought them into Buzz City. They were super helpful and offered my kids some promo materials as they searched for what they wanted. They answered all my questions and were very knowledgeable about the cards we bought. My kids left overjoyed and told me this was the best day ever! Thank you Buzz City Games.

Bought a few singles from them with 1 being evolving skies. As soon as I went to rip it I could immediately tell it was a resealed pack. Code card was in the front instead of the back and there were cards not even from the set in the pack. It also had a code card that signifies a hit but I didn’t have a hit or even a reverse. A few cards didn’t even look or feel real. (Left is the resealed card and right is from my old bulk).

Just finished our first-ever puzzle competition at Buzz City Games, and the experience was so awesome! We’ve been customers at this shop for about a year now, and I mean it when I say they not only have a great selection of something for everyone—from board games to Dungeons and Dragons merch to puzzles to Warhammer—but they also have a great staff. Everyone here is so welcoming and incredibly helpful. If you’re looking for a local business to support, definitely stop by their store. So happy we could be part of their (and our) first puzzle competition!

Do not buy from them online. They will take your money, and then wait a month to tell you it’s out of stock, and then you’ll wait days for a refund. I found them on Amazon. DO NOT BUY, you’ve been warned.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Jonathan, 
I’m sorry to hear about your experience with Amazon. This review may be a bit misdirected as Amazon took and canceled the preorder. Please reach out to info@buzzcitygames.com so we can help.

reviews_data.review_text: Great game shop in the heart of downtown Concord. Staff is super friendly and willing to help you find something that fits your needs. I wish I knew all the names of the employees, but Stephanie and Kasey/Casey are awesome. Would recommend.

Buzz City is one of the best local game stores in my area! They have tons of different puzzles, tabletop games, tcg, dice, playmats, sleeves, deckboxes, miniatures, campaign books... pretty much everything you could think of related to gaming. They host a wide variety of tournaments and events as well. The staff is always welcoming and eager to help.
They had what I was looking for at a great price point and also had cases available. Would go there daily if I was closer. Awesome selection of things to buy for everyone
Awesome local place!

This place saved my kid's weekend! After being majorly bummed out by a different game shop, we came here as a nearby backup search and it was exactly what we were looking for. We'll definitely need to plan future trips with the density of their collection.
Store was great! It’s located in an old bank and seeing all the old vaults and architecture was awesome! Just wish they sold pokemon singles as well!
I haven’t been here, but I bought from them online and they were helpful and nice. I really appreciated them.
Shhhhh this is the spot though
Love this place tons of games and very knowledgeable staff

I am primarily a board gamer, and they have an excellent slection of board games and fair pricing. The staff is amazing, all of them are kind and helpful. Simply the best place around for any tabletop hobbys.
Wonderfully helpful staff and lots of game selections.

Awesome hidden gem of a store in the historic area of Concord! A wide and varies selection of tabletop, board, and TCG games! All the accessories you could want as well from minis, paint, dice, plushies and collectibles figures! It is super clean, well laid out and it's so cool to be in an old bank. Customer service is also top notch and very knowledgeable. Definitely give this place a look!

I was on the MTG Companion app and was looking for a place to play magic. I saw this place and thought it would be cool but then I saw that it says $50 per round to play.  It also looks like they charge $10 just to get a seat at the table. I still want to go in and check out their selection of cards so I will update my review. 1 star for ridiculous pricing just to play.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi J W, Please stop by or reach out so we can get the companion app events clarified. We don't have a per round charge, nor a $10 seat at the table charge for our open playspace.

reviews_data.review_text: It's literally the best. We drive a ways to come see what's new or buy gifts every few weeks.Plus great service and staff.
Great shop to buy from and play at. The staff is great. They stick to their word and honor their customers to the best of their ability. Thank you Buzz City!
Great selection at reasonable prices!

I have come to this store a few times now and had a pleasant experience until more recent times.

I am a Bandai games player, dabbling in Digimon, One Piece and recently Dragon Ball Fusion world.

The upcharge on Bandai product has become absurd. I recently obtained product from competing stores for the proper retail pricing, at $120 for a booster box and 14.99 for the recent starter decks.
Buzz City games is charging 24.99 per starter, and bearly $180 after tax for their boosters.
Buzz City is also charging near double original MSRP for upcoming preorders of OP-7 for one piece. They do not even host play for these card games anymore, or at the very least do not advertise it anymore. They are profiting off of the scarcity and limitation of product.

It’s incredibly frustrating for stores to follow this kind of practice. And as I’m told by previous players of digimon, this is something the store has a history of with limited product, charging nearly double retail for the original set release of Digimon as well.

I highly recommend price checking with other retailers and no longer giving this store your business if they are going to continue these practices. Support other Bandai stores so that they cannot receive product anymore and thus cannot continue to attempt to scalp it without regard to the player base.

There are locations nearly 8 minutes away that would be a better option for you than continuing to support bad business practice.

As for any future replies to this review, just consider this. Any explanation for a price raise in comparison to all of the stores that actually support play, selling for actual retail should hold absolutely no merit in your book. Don’t fall for the spin.
Great place and fun!
Went in for a few items today, they had Great customer service and were very friendly. Thank you.
Best place in town for games wonderful community and food/restaurants as well

Buzz City has a great selection. I was able to get my last 2 Cyberpunk RED expansion books here! They also have great recommendations for other board games. Customer service is amazing and the staff is very knowledgable.

Sam said it was a good store.

My son worked at a game store elsewhere and was impressed with this one.
I liked the old bank building use.
Super cool vibe and a great selection. Staff is knowledgeable and friendly. There’s truly something for everyone here!!
Super fun place and awesome staff
Went in to check out the shop and was not disappointed. There is a great selection of products at a fair price, and the staff is very friendly and helpful.
I’m sure I was annoying with the number of questions I asked but the lady in the store was super helpful and you can tell she was passionate about her work. Nice little place.
Hey if you're going to use the best offer feature at least send a counter offer instead of just blocking people, it really makes you guys seem pathetic.
Great place to hangout with friends, great vibes
My son and I played in the Lorcana league event on Monday night. We had fun and he likes it even more now. The other players were nice. I’m looking forward to going back!
So many games to choose from! Such a cool place to visit. Very organized and well stocked. Walked out with four new games and a plushie. I wish there was a store like it in my city.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you very much, glad you enjoyed it!

reviews_data.review_text: They didn't have one piece tcg
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Red, We do have a few starter decks and booster packs in-stock for One Piece. Feel free to reach out via phone 980-439-8946 or email info@buzzcitygames.com so we can get assist you.

reviews_data.review_text: Beautiful looking card shop. Definitely one of the most unique looking card shops I ever been to. The fact they have a bank vault is the coolest thing for a card shop. They have lots of different product and plenty of room to play especially upstairs where they have extra tables. Customer service was fantastic. Both employees had a lot of knowledge and let me know about different events they had going on. Especially Lachrisa who was very knowledgeable on some board games I was thinking about purchasing as well as some D&D books that I was looking at. I look forward to doing more business with buzz city!

Incredibly welcoming and helpful staff, Andrew helped me out with a nearly impossible to find game, and it was a fantastic experience.  Lightning fast shipping and delivery as well. Will definitely be grabbing more games from them in the future.

Thank you!
Went in to look at warhammer range, noticed several products priced above GW retail.   Update- Buzz City are promptly addressing this issue, thanks guys
Terrible service , workers are keeping tournament prizes for themselfs and charging tcg prices for newly released sealed products! Hard to support lgs that's price gouging like the scalpers!
Really cool place to find board and other games. They do not have video games.

If I could leave a higher review, I would. I preordered a card for $70 that had a price of $700 at release and they honored this purchase. I have been burned by other stores before, but the respect I have for the team here is unparalleled. I may be states away, but you have earned a TCGPlayer customer for life.
I have made so many great friends coming here and I hope to make more as I keep on coming.
Very relaxed little game store in an outstanding location. Not a huge play space, but pretty good inventory, and some of the best prices in Charlotte.

This store is *so* cool.  Situated in an old bank in downtown Concord, walking into the place is like going back in time 70 years.  But instead of stiff bankers, it's filled with fantasy and sci-fi goodness.  The interior has a huge vaulting ceiling and a massive bank vault.  Building design aside, it has a great selection of stuff, and a literal vault of stock.  Staff is super helpful and friendly.  There's a modest amount of play space.  Only minus is parking because of being in a downtown setting, but a free parking deck is only half a block away.  It's definitely one of the best gaming stores in town.
Great staff and really good prices.
Cute shop, great dice. We love the staff here.
Really dope vibes, awesome selection, kickass architecture.
Nice place with a huge selection of board games, card games, and puzzles. They occasionally hold events here to play test developing games with raffles.

Can't say enough good things about this place, the staff, and the other people who come here. When I moved down here I was looking for a new community to be apart of and I was welcomed with open arms. If you get the chance come in and hang out,game and meet new people you won't regret it!

5 stars isn’t enough stars for this place. I’ve made so great friends here, staff included, I’ve gotten work opportunities here, played a bunch of games that blew my mind…I can attribute so much of my current livelihood to Buzz City which might sound a little crazy, but I mean it! Come to Tuesday board game night! It’s a seriously great crowd.
Great place super nice and kind
It's a really neat store, and my boyfriend loves coming here.
Great shop with fair prices and always have the cards I want.  You can play magic, Pokémon or whatever your heart desires in a friendly atmosphere.
Legitimately one of the best game shops that I've ever visited.  Terrific customer service and competitive prices.

Buzz City Games is a great store with a fun and inclusive environment. I love the staff as they are both friendly and open to topics spanning from Magic:The Gathering to DND to random and niche board games. I have made so many great friends coming here and I hope to make more as I keep on coming.
Really great people who show up for events and staff is fun and helpful for not just product information, but any question for any game possible. ❤️😘 Tim
A friendly game store with a wonderful atmosphere, helpful and kind employees, as well as lots of events across many different hobbies.

I've only been here twice, so far. The staff has been very helpful and nice. They may not have the largest selection of games but I have found some locally hard to find games here. They have a store account that allows you to earn discounts. Also, the staff isn't bugging you every 5 minutes while you are browsing, which I like. I'd recommend going and giving their shelves a good browse, you may find something you like.

If you're local or just visiting downtown Concord, Buzz City Games is a must for unique games, puzzles, and Squishables!

They also have social events every week and is a great place to make friends. Everyone who works here is extremely informative, friendly, and welcoming!
You'll be in here quite a while due to the plethora of games. There were also tables with a few different games that you can try out. That's smart of them to do that. Staff was friendly.

SO MANY GAMES! Love this place! It absolutely blasted us off into the world of board games, now we have a whole closet full! So glad we have a local place like this and hope to get the chance to participate in one of their game nights or DnD sessions!
Wonderful staff, amazing selection of games, positive atmosphere!

Found this store on an absolute whim, and SO glad we did. My husband and I are relatively new to the tabletop world, played checkers and monopoly and such growing up, but getting our first deck-building game Dominion 2 years ago, Gloomhaven, and then Star Realms. There are aspects of all of these that we enjoy, and aspects that we don't. Finally decided to find a store for expert opinions, and boy howdy, did Buzz City come THROUGH.walked in and was blown away by the many fully stocked shelves, and quickly felt out of our depth. Until Stephanie (a staff member)  introduced herself and happily walked us through the store and pulled in a client, and even a regular customer/ player to  tell us about the games and made EXCELLENT recommendations, and told us about the standing game nights that are open to learn and to play. It really felt like a community more than a store. Will definitely be back.
The staff is awesome. I go up to play Yugioh and depite not knowing the most they are super understanding and helpful. Such a fun and welcoming environment
Best games ever
reviews_data.owner_answer: Best review ever

reviews_data.review_text: I love the great ambience of the old bank building, the awesome board game selection that changes, and the nice staff. I also appreciate that they enforce masks. My happy place!
Staff is very friendly and always helpful. Great place for MTG EDH and they have an insane collection of board and card games. Easily the best card shop in Concord.
Great staff, fun events and awesome Catalog of all table top player needs

Cool store, super helpful people.
Lots of interesting games and puzzles you won’t find anywhere else.

A wide selection of games, exceedingly
Knowledgeable & friendly staff! For my money, the absolute best FLG in NC.

I loved it there! I expressed interest in DND, and was pointed all around the store and told about all the cool things they had! I definitely would recommend! The environment is so open and welcoming there!

Incredible selection of board games and puzzles and super nice and helpful staff.
Bought a fun game I hadn’t seen anywhere else. Thanks!
The customer service was excellent and the people there were very polite. And I was happy that they were all about safety with the masks.
Stay away... Not a ,=== place at all.. they are very unhealthy and unclean.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Michael, We are sorry to hear that you disagree with policy requring masks to be worn in our retail store. We wish you all the best and a happy and healthy holiday.

reviews_data.review_text: I loved the feel of the place, I have only been twice but, the miniatures and card/ board games they have are incredible!
Great business, Owner is engaged and very professional. Always felt like I was taken care of. Highly recommend for family atmosphere and product selection.
Great location, staff, and gaming apparel/supplies. Swing through, you won’t be disappointed.
Clean and has a lot of variety and the customer service is great
Great store and staff. Largest selection of board/card games and collectibles I've seen in a long while. Worth a trip for anyone.
This was my first time going to buzz city and everyone was friendly! They had everything I wanted plus more! And they have a membership! This will be my official store!!!!

Buzz City is my favorite game store in the area. Super friendly and helpful staff, insane selection, and reasonable prices.  You can go in and just pick a game from the demo shelf and start playing, and a staff member will even help you get started with the rules if you want. Plus, the building is an old bank, so the aesthetic is great! If you're in downtown Concord, stop in, you'll leave happier than when you arrived!

Great store! Fantastic selection! Super friendly and knowledgeable staff! I'm not local but if I was this would definitely be my local game store!! Can't describe how impressed I was with the environment and staff!
Yeah the site says they buy pokemon cards and we get here and the dude was rude and couldn't help us with anything..
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Tina, Unfortunately, we don't purchase single Pokemon cards, please reach out to info@buzzcitygames.com so we can correct any incorrect site information. I apprecaite the feedback and will work with our staff for future interactions.

reviews_data.review_text: Extremely nice and well priced. If you can't find a board game here, it doesn't exist.
Helpful staff
This is easily the best card store I have ever been to for magic buying and selling they don't rip you off like some other card stores do on prices
Love this place! Much friendlier and personable than other shops in the area. Never have an issue with customer service, prices, or product availability!

I try to visit this place as often as I can in an effort to support local. The. Staff is beyond friendly and very helpful when answering mine or anyone else’s questions about their card and board games.

I and my gal love this store. We make it a point to visit it anytime we are in the area.  It has a great selection of games, from the simpler games for children and party games to the complex, "crunchy" games preferred by hobbyist gamers.

They also have the largest selection of high-quality puzzles that I have seen anywhere.

If you like games or puzzles,  you owe it to yourself to check out this store.
Great place it was a old bank they keep there Magic cards in the vault. Huge selection of games you will really like the place.
Staff was terrific, good selection.  Lots of product on the floor blocking shelves though. Seems like they need more storage.

I ordered from these guys through Amazon and was promised my product by today. I checked the tracking info to see if I could get an estimate of time and they hadn’t even bothered handing it over to Amazon for shipping. Highly unprofessional
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Ryan, Please reach out to Amazon directly, as your order is FBA (Fulfilled by Amazon) and Buzz City doesn't have access to the shipment details for your order. You can reach us directly at info@buzzcitygames.com if it isn't resolved by Amazon Customer Service.

reviews_data.review_text: Scalping prices for Digimon boosters that just released. charging 165 when msrp about 71. More than x2 the price. Really no way to treat customers.
reviews_data.owner_answer: For the out of print product you are referring to, the current market price is $191/box. We typically charge less than market price when products are no longer in-print. Feel free to reach out to info@buzzcitygames.com and I'm happy to further discuss your experience with you.

reviews_data.review_text:
Scammed me out of $80.00
Ordered a Wahammer 40K box set over a month ago and it was missing the hero sprue so I sent it back, they sent another box missing the same sprue so I returned for a refund... I am still waiting for my money. Beware of scams.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We are happy to liason with Games Workshop regarding missing pieces, please reach out directly to info@buzzcitygames.com

reviews_data.review_text: Great place, good selection, friendly staff, highly recommended checking it out.
Great staff. They listen to you and give great recommendations! If they don't have it, they're happy to try and order it. Also awesome communication. Wish I could give more than 5 stars.

Pretty awesome space even during COVID. The highlights and areas to improve upon:
+They have reserved rooms for people calling ahead!
+great selection! Carrying a HUGE selection of games from Catan and warhammer to Battle tech and star wars legion.
-The bathroom, or at least the men's bathroom did not look like it had been cleaned recently, which is an issue even without COVID. The men's bathroom uses a hot air dryer to remove water after washing your hands, which is fine, but an option for a paper towel would be appreciated as there are articles suggesting germa are spread by air hand driers.
+hours of operation on Sunday. Sunday is a day usually most places close early and Buzzcity is open till 9pm!
+carry Bobsmith glue and glue accelerator!
-For now they have only 2 rooms it seems to reserve which is an issue if you are not fast to reserve a room.

Overall a 4/5 stars. A star lost due to the bathroom issues, and one star due to limited play area., but they at least have space open so 4/5 stars!
Great selection, friendly folks.  Awesome location too.  They kept the old bank design and I think that's really original.  Definitely my go to place for games.
Friendly staff and great product selection!

I frikin love this store. When you trade in your cards for in-store credit they don’t cheap out on you and the staff do their best to find what you need/want. I was there the other day, and I traded in a couple expensive cards for in-store credit and I honestly got a couple dollars more than I thought they were worth, I was planning on using the credit to purchase A LOT of cards that day. Not only that but they were a little over an hour away from closing and I felt super guilty but the staff reassured me it was no problem at all. They found me all 40+cards in almost no time flat, I’m going to keep coming until they don’t want me anymore or I buy them out. I suffer from really bad anxiety, specially the social kind and they made me feel so welcomed that I have no issues in keeping coming back. Hey guys if y’all are reading this it’s the guy who took home yalls “Nahiri, heir of the ancients” foil borderless and a bunch of other cards for a deck home and asked for more of Nahiris in the future. Thank you for your great service.
Great inventory and setting. The old Bank safe is impressive. They offer play space upstairs. Staff was knowledgeable and helpful.
Have visited several times and it's a fun visit! Good selection of games and cards.
I love these guys.

An extraordinary selection of board and card games, and super friendly, helpful staff. We've bought many games here, and love to drop in and try out new games. The perfect place to find gifts for everyone who likes games or puzzles.
Awesome location and selection. We go to a lot of game stores, and it's really nice to be in a space that is clean and well-lit.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the kind words and for stopping by. We are always looking to improve, feel free to reach out to info@buzzcitygames.com to let us know what we could have done better. -Andrew

reviews_data.review_text: Helpful and knowledgeable staff. Will be shopping here for my magic and gaming needs.

Went in looking for a copy of a promo card and was told they were out.  Yet there were copies being held for "regulars".  This is against the suppliers policy.  Will be reporting this to said supplier and will never set foot back in this waste of space.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Kevin, I’m sorry to hear about your experience, that doesn’t sound like a policy that we have in place. Please reach out to info@buzzcitygames.com with information about the particular promo and we can get you squared away.  Best! -Andrew

reviews_data.review_text: Big variety of different types of games
Run by a great guy who was able to answer all of my questions. Don't let the chaos gods know he has a favorite.
Super helpful staff, good selection!
Great selection of gaming supplies. Fabulous dice. Great customer service.
Great people and great service. very friendly

This place is awesome! Lots of good games and puzzles, including many you've probably never heard of. They have a lot of demo games to play so its fun just to hang out there. Staff is super knowledgeable  and is great at helping you find new games. New location in the old bank is also very cool.
Very Friendly staff. Nice selection. Definitely worth stopping by.
Very cool place, friendly staff, and good selection of products. Magic is their main focus, but they have sealed Pokemon, Yu-Gi-Oh, and board game products.
Great store! They gave us a free demo escape room card game too. If we lived near Concord, we'd be here often!
Nice and friendly staff. Good selection.

This place is great. Its used to be so hard to find good game stores anywhere in Concord, until Buzz City Games popped up right in the middle of downtown. My one issue is the prices, sometimes more than double that of a physical copy on Amazon, However, this is easily excusable by the many services they provide for free such as Adventurers League and Tables that are always open for personal use.
A classic game store. Dice, paints, board games, and tables to play at. They also allow guests to play some demo board games in store so you can try before you buy.
Great store, great staff and selection of items.

Fun and inviting place. They try their best to make you feel welcome in their establishment and I think they do a good job of it. If you're looking for a fun place to hang out and play trading card games, board games, or are new to them; come in and the staff there will be happy to engage with you. (If you play magic the gathering come draft on Friday nights!)

I've been here twice and both times, the employees have taken time to either sit me down and go through the player's handbook for 20 minutes or look up some info for me. Very helpful and knowledgeable!
Love this place come every weekend to spend our weekly dice budget. Andrew is awesome and  bends over backwards for his customers.

I think it's a good place.
There's a lot of board games to choose from, seating for 20-30 people (by my estimate), and friendly staff.  Has regular events for people to join.  Has pleny of Magic: The Gathering support, but that's not the only thing going on here (just my hobby).
There's lots of parking at nearby lots on the weekends, and a few places to eat nearby for long game days.
The only limitation is it closes in the late afternoon, but if the hours work for you it's a great place to play and shop.
Awsome help. Answered all my questions. Lots or selection.
Super friendly local game store.  Great place to hang out and play board games, Magic , etc.

I stoped by the store on a whim to see if they had the game of GO, and THEY DID!!! Large selection of games. Fun place to visit with very friendly staff! Highly recommend for people to stop by and check it out.
Andrew(the owner) is super friendly and helpful, also willing to run through any game you purchase and teach it to you. Nice aesthetic to the store and in a good area so it’s a nice hang out spot!

Great staff and huge selection of board games and RPGs. Large play area with tables and chairs setup where you can demo games or play your own. Staff is very knowledgeable and ready to answer any questions. Highly recommend this store for your gaming needs. D&D adventures league is on Tuesdays and Thursdays and it's a great time.
Nice and knowledgeable staff! Great selection of games.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for stopping by!

reviews_data.review_text: It's literally the best. We drive a ways to come see what's new or buy gifts every few weeks.Plus great service and staff.

I have come to this store a few times now and had a pleasant experience until more recent times.

I am a Bandai games player, dabbling in Digimon, One Piece and recently Dragon Ball Fusion world.

The upcharge on Bandai product has become absurd. I recently obtained product from competing stores for the proper retail pricing, at $120 for a booster box and 14.99 for the recent starter decks.
Buzz City games is charging 24.99 per starter, and bearly $180 after tax for their boosters.
Buzz City is also charging near double original MSRP for upcoming preorders of OP-7 for one piece. They do not even host play for these card games anymore, or at the very least do not advertise it anymore. They are profiting off of the scarcity and limitation of product.

It’s incredibly frustrating for stores to follow this kind of practice. And as I’m told by previous players of digimon, this is something the store has a history of with limited product, charging nearly double retail for the original set release of Digimon as well.

I highly recommend price checking with other retailers and no longer giving this store your business if they are going to continue these practices. Support other Bandai stores so that they cannot receive product anymore and thus cannot continue to attempt to scalp it without regard to the player base.

There are locations nearly 8 minutes away that would be a better option for you than continuing to support bad business practice.

As for any future replies to this review, just consider this. Any explanation for a price raise in comparison to all of the stores that actually support play, selling for actual retail should hold absolutely no merit in your book. Don’t fall for the spin.

The only limitation is it closes in the late afternoon, but if the hours work for you it's a great place to play and shop.
Awsome help. Answered all my questions. Lots or selection.
Super friendly local game store.  Great place to hang out and play board games, Magic , etc.

I stoped by the store on a whim to see if they had the game of GO, and THEY DID!!! Large selection of games. Fun place to visit with very friendly staff! Highly recommend for people to stop by and check it out.
Andrew(the owner) is super friendly and helpful, also willing to run through any game you purchase and teach it to you. Nice aesthetic to the store and in a good area so it’s a nice hang out spot!

Great staff and huge selection of board games and RPGs. Large play area with tables and chairs setup where you can demo games or play your own. Staff is very knowledgeable and ready to answer any questions. Highly recommend this store for your gaming needs. D&D adventures league is on Tuesdays and Thursdays and it's a great time.
Nice and knowledgeable staff! Great selection of games.
